<p>The shadow of 2013 elections will loom over politics. Fernando Lugo's left-wing administration, lacking a majority and weakened by an ill-advised attempt to lift the constitutional bar on his candidacy for a second term, will be in no position to advance social and economic reforms. Expansionary fiscal policy will stay in place in the run-up to the election, raising the risk of a hard landing afterwards.Â </p>

